result.execSummary:
The defendant Laura B. Schnell was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Business Setting >$10,000 [Modifiers: Penalty - Theft >$10,000], a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
Pay restitution in the amount of $90,899.68 and restitution surcharge. Restitution is subject to the Defendant's right to challenge.  
----------------------------------
*AMENDMENT - 04/04/2016 -  Pursuant to Restitution Hearing held on 03/15/2016 and the Order adopting Findings of Fact and Conclusions of Law filed 03/30/2016, the Defendant has the ability to pay restitution to Axcess Financial in the amount of $67,204.84 at $500.00 per month unless otherwise ordered by the court or probation agent.

As requested by Access Financial, DOC should distribute restitution payments to:  
Attn:  Shannon Towe - Senior Risk Director
Axcess Financial
7755 Montgomery Road
Suite 400
Cincinnati, OH  45236
----------------------------------

Pay court costs.   If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment may be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for the balance due.  Collections may include income assignment.
----------------------------------

IT IS HEREBY ORDERED THAT the defendant's excess work release funds be applied to any & all outstanding Court obligations while serving his mandatory jail sentence.
----------------------------------

Provide biological specimen to state crime lab for DNA analysis, and pay DNA analysis surcharge.   Counseling as recommended by Probation Agent.   The defendant must pay Department of Corrections Supervision fees.
----------------------------------
